Package radin.core.input

Class Tokenizer<T>

java.lang.Object
Tokenizer<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the treeType to output. If T extends Token then the getKeywordToken(String) is usable
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<T>, Iterator<T>, ICompilationErrorCollector, ITokenizer<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
BasicLexer, PreprocessingLexer
public abstract class Tokenizer<T>
extends Object
implements ITokenizer<T>
The abstract class any Tokenizer must inherit in order to be used

    • getKeywordToken

      public static Token getKeywordToken​(String image)
      Gets a token based on a image. If it's defined as a keyword, it returns a keyword token. Otherwise it returns a TokenType.t_id token
      Parameters:
      image - the input image
      Returns:
      the appropriate token
